{"title":"Ergon takes MTB comfort to Infinergy and beyond with new SMC Core saddles","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/10/ergon-takes-mtb-comfort-to-infinergy-and-beyond-with-new-smc-core-saddles/","date":1615392016000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>Ever since BASF’s Infinergy expanded thermoplastic polyurethane (E-TPU) material popped up, a number of companies have been figuring out new ways to use it. From the midsoles of your favorite shoes, to the core of a tennis racket, or as part of a bicycle saddle, the material promises light weight, responsive comfort with excellent damping properties. Ergon is one of those companies and has been <a href=\"https://ergonbike.shop/collections/smc-core\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">including Infinergy foam as part of their Core saddle constructions for a few years</a> – and now it’s coming to mountain bikes.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side.jpg\" alt=\"Ergon SMC Core MTB saddle side\" width=\"720\" height=\"392\" sizes=\"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side.jpg 720w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side-297x162.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side-120x65.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side-696x379.jpg 696w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side.jpg 720w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side-297x162.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side-120x65.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103643/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-side-696x379.jpg 696w\"></a>OK, technically, Ergon already had a Core saddle aimed towards mountain biking, but for bikes with a motor in the SM E-Mountain Core Prime. The new SMC Core Men’s and Women’s saddles are built with a slightly different shape and construction, specifically tailored towards the needs of human powered mountain bikers looking for increased comfort.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle.jpg\" alt=\"Ergon SMC Core MTB saddle diagonal\" width=\"1024\" height=\"745\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-297x216.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-800x582.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-120x87.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-768x559.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-696x506.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-577x420.jpg 577w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-324x235.jpg 324w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-297x216.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-800x582.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-120x87.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-768x559.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-696x506.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-577x420.jpg 577w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103732/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-324x235.jpg 324w\"></a></p><p>Utilizing their Core and TwinShell technology, the saddles layer BASF Infinergy between two shells made from nylon composite. Then Ergon’s orthopedic comfort foam is layered on top with a microfiber cover. The layered TwinShell design allows for the saddle to rotate along with your pelvis which is said to reduce pressure on your sit bones and genital area.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103648/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-top.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103648/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-top.jpg\" alt=\"Ergon SMC Core MTB saddle top\" width=\"1024\" height=\"661\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10103648/Ergon-bike-SMC-Core-MTB-comfort-mountain-bike-saddle-top.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazona